      "name": "Synthesis of prior pedicle screw FEA validation studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis aggregating findings from more than a dozen independent pedicle screw finite-element validation studies published between 2005 and 2022, covering a range of screw geometries, materials, and loading configurations. The synthesis establishes baseline model-form plausibility for titanium alloy pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending and provides the prior credibility context against which the present COU1 results are interpreted. Material property distributions, contact algorithm choices, and boundary condition sensitivities are all informed by this body of prior work. Given the breadth and depth of the underlying literature, this node is treated operationally as a well-established evidence base."
